fix(rules): cross-platform basename for command-allowlist

path.basename() is platform-aware and only splits on the native
separator, so on POSIX a Windows-style path like C:\Windows\cmd.exe
was being treated as a single filename. That made the shell
detection miss cmd.exe/powershell.exe, so the "flags windows
absolute paths" test failed on Linux/macOS CI runners.

Replace with a manual basename that accepts both / and \, so rules
behave identically regardless of host OS.

Also refine dependabot.yml:
- Drop include: scope to avoid double-prefixed commits
  (chore(deps)(deps): ...).
- Ignore major version bumps; security alerts still surface via the
  Dependabot alerts feed, majors go through manual review.
